Injecting Gain Drifts¶

We inject drifts with a $1/f$ dependence with $f_{knee}=150 $ mHz (see PSD below) on all detectors within a detector pair .

The input signal encodes: Monopole + Dipole + CMB T fluctuations. So far, no noise is injected to data.

We estimated maps with MADAM destriper (baseline=60 sec)

Mitigating leakage¶

To mitigate the leakage we estimate the gain by regressing the signal against a template encoding the CMB T with $\ell \gtrsim 50$.

Below are the mitigation steps to a generic TOD $d_t$:

  • Consider a small chunk of $d_t$ corresponding to a given timescale $\tau$ of 20 min.
  • Apply a high-pass filter to $d_{t , t+\tau} $ with cutoff frequency $f_{c}=10$ mHz $^{(1)}$
  • Regress $d_{t , t+\tau} $ against the template estimate the slope $g$
  • Correct $d_{t , t+\tau} $ for the gain factor $g$

$^{(1)}$ Given an $\ell_c$ (to retain only signal @ $\ell> \ell_c$ ) we estimate $ f_c$ as : $$ \ell_c = 2 \pi f_c/ \omega_{scan} $$ $\omega_{scan} $ is the scanning speed and it 's defined as : $$ \omega_{scan} = \sin (\beta ) * spinrate = 0.0013 rad/sec =0.07 deg/sec$$ Where $\beta$ is the angle between the boresight and the spin axis (50 deg according to latest values) , and the spin rate is 0.1 rpm .

thus, if $\ell_c=50$ , $f_c= 10$ mHz

#%matplotlib notebook 

fs = 20.  ; fknee=0.15; fcutoff=0.01


def showTOD(det):
     
    dicx = {0 :'A', 1:'B',  }
    cmbt=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/tod_cmbonly.npy') [0]
    drift=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/corr/0.15/outtod_drifts.npy') [0]
    mit=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/corr/0.15/outtod_mitig.npy') [0]
    N=len(mit[1])
    
    fig =pl.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(122); 
    ax2 = ax1.twiny() ;
    
    ax2.set_xlabel(r'$\ell$', fontsize=15); 
    ax1.set_xlabel('f [Hz] ', fontsize=15); 
    ax1.set_ylabel('PSD ['+r'$K \sqrt{s}$]', fontsize=15)
    #pl.subplot(122)

    pl.suptitle('Det{}'.format(dicx[det]))
    freq, driftspec= signal.periodogram(drift[det]  ,fs=fs, scaling='density')
    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(driftspec),  alpha=.7 , label='unfilt.'  )
    freq, mitspec= signal.periodogram(mit[det] ,fs=fs, scaling='density')

    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(mitspec),  alpha=.7 , label='filt.'   )

    freq, fspectrum= signal.periodogram(( cmbt[det])[:N] ,fs=fs, scaling='density')
    #ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(fspectrum),     alpha=.5
    #           , color='black' , label='CMB '  )
    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.ones_like(freq)*3.8e-5,'r--', alpha=.3, linewidth=3, label='NET ' )
    ax2.loglog(2.*pl.pi*freq/0.0013, pl.zeros_like(freq) ); 
    pl.legend() 

    ax1.grid()

    pl.ylim([1e-10,1])

    
    pl.subplot(121)
    t_array = pl.arange(N)/fs/60.
    pl.plot(t_array ,     drift[det]-2.725, label='unfilt. w/o Monopole' ) 

    pl.plot(t_array ,     mit[det], alpha=.6, label='filt.' ) 
    #t_array = pl.arange(len(cmbt[0] ))/fs/60.
    #pl.plot(t_array ,     (cmbt[det] ) [:N], alpha=.5, color='black', label='CMB'  )

    pl.grid()
    #pl.ylim([-.01,.01])

    pl.xlabel('time [min]')
    pl.ylabel('TOD [ K ]')
    pl.legend()
    pl.tight_layout()

#w= interact (showTOD, det=[('A', 0), ('B', 1) ]) 

showTOD(0)
showTOD(1)

Fig1 (top) and (bottom) panels show 10 minutes of time samples and their respective PSD for a pair of detectors. (solid blue) is the signal w/ gaindrifts encoding Monopole (which has been subtracted for graphical purposes ) Dipole and CMB temperature fluctuations, (solid orange) is the timestream after the high pass filter and the regression correction applied. Notice that in the PSD as expected all the modes with $\ell < 50$ have been filtered. As a reference we show as dashed red line the $38 \mu K \sqrt{s}$ NET level for a LB detector.

def showperpair(Pair):
     
    dicx = {  0:'sum',  1:'diff'   }
    cmbt=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/tod_cmbonly.npy') [0]
    drift=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/corr/0.15/outtod_drifts.npy') [0]
    mit=   pl.load('/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/corr/0.15/outtod_mitig.npy') [0]
    if  Pair :
        driftdiff= .5*(drift[1] -drift[0])
        cmbtdiff = .5*(cmbt[1] -cmbt[0])
        mitdiff  = .5*(mit[1] -mit[0])
         
    else:
        driftdiff= .5*(drift[1] +drift[0]) - 2.725
        cmbtdiff = .5*(cmbt[1] +cmbt[0])
        mitdiff  = .5*(mit[1] +mit[0]) 
    
    N=len(mit[1])
    
    fig =pl.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(122); 
    ax2 = ax1.twiny() ;
    
    ax2.set_xlabel(r'$\ell$', fontsize=15); 
    ax1.set_xlabel('f [Hz] ', fontsize=15); 
    ax1.set_ylabel('PSD ['+r'$K \sqrt{s}$]', fontsize=15)
    pl.suptitle('Pair {}'.format(dicx[Pair]))
    freq, driftspec= signal.periodogram(driftdiff  ,fs=fs, scaling='density')
    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(driftspec),  alpha=.7, label='unfilt.'    )
    freq, mitspec= signal.periodogram(mitdiff ,fs=fs, scaling='density')

    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(mitspec),  alpha=.7 , label=' filt.'   )

    freq, fspectrum= signal.periodogram(( cmbtdiff)[:N] ,fs=fs, scaling='density')
    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.sqrt(fspectrum),     alpha=.5
               , color='black'  , label='CMB' )

    ax1.loglog(freq, pl.ones_like(freq)*3.8e-5,'r--', alpha=.3, linewidth=3, label='NET ' )
    ax2.loglog(2.*pl.pi*freq/0.0013, pl.zeros_like(freq) ); 
    pl.legend()
    
    ax1.grid()

    pl.ylim([1e-10,1])

    
    pl.subplot(121)
    t_array = pl.arange(N)/fs/60.
    pl.plot(t_array ,    driftdiff, label='unfilt. w/o Monopole' ) 

    pl.plot(t_array ,     mitdiff, alpha=.6, label='filt.' ) 
    #t_array = pl.arange(len(cmbt[0] ))/fs/60.
    pl.plot(t_array ,     (cmbtdiff ) [:N], alpha=.3, color='black', label='CMB'  )

    pl.grid()
    #pl.ylim([-.01,.01])

    pl.xlabel('time [min]')
    pl.ylabel('TOD [ K ]')
    pl.legend()
    pl.tight_layout()
#w= interact (showperpair, Pair=[('sum', 0), ('diff', 1) ]) 

showperpair(0)
showperpair(1)

(solid blue) is the signal w/ gaindrifts encoding Monopole ( subtracted for graphical purposes on the top panel ) Dipole and CMB temperature fluctuations, (solid orange) is the timestream after the high pass filter and the regression correction applied. Notice that in the PSD as expected all the modes with $\ell < 50$ have been filtered. As a reference we show as dashed red line the $38 \mu K \sqrt{s}$ NET level for a LB detector.We also show in solid gray the PSD of CMB intensity ( top panel) and CMB Polarization signal (bottom panel).

def showmap(maps ):
     
    dicx = {0:'018', 1:'001' }
    if maps:
        s='uncorr'
    else:
        s='corr'
    driftmap = hp.read_map(field=range(3) , 
                           filename='/Users/peppe/work/satellite_sims/drifting_gain/'+s+'/0.15/madam_map_'+dicx[maps]+'.fits', 
                           verbose=False)
    fig= pl.figure(figsize=(14,6 ) )
    hp.mollview(driftmap  [0] , unit='K',title=r'$  T$',  sub=131,fig=fig   ,cmap=cmap    )

    hp.mollview(driftmap  [1] , unit='K',title=r'$  Q  $',  sub=132,fig=fig , min=-5e-5, max=5e-5 ,cmap=cmap    )
